**************************************************************************
**************** Installation on Linux System ****************************

Install / Updating npm: (node package manager)
npm install -g npm

Install CLI (Command line interface)
npm install -g @angular/cli

to update CLI
npm uninstall -g @angular/cli
npm cache verify
npm install -g @angular/cli@next
**************************************************************************

**************************************************************************
********** Steps to Build and Execute Typescript Applications ************

To compile TypeScript into JavaScript you need to have TypeScript installed.

To install TypeScript using the Node Package Manager (npm) type the command:
npm install -g typescript

Now we can use the 'tsc' command to transcribe TypeScript into Javascript.
tsc Name_Of_File.ts

After successful transcompilation new file of javascript gets generated as Name_Of_File.js

To execute the javascript application use below command as:
node Name_Of_File.js
**************************************************************************
